Karel: [https://msr-redmond.github.io/karel-dataset/](https://msr-redmond.github.io/karel-dataset/)

- Gridworld DSL  
- PS compatibility: Solutions are DSL programs built from primitives (move, turnLeft, pickMarker, putMarker) composed via control flow (while, if, repeat), each subroutine IS a PS routine, and shared spatial primitives with ARC (grid traversal, boundary detection, marker manipulation) mean concepts could directly transfer.  
- Verifier: binary pass/fail

Math: wedsacf/competition\_math

- Mathematical reasoning  
- PS compatibility: Highly subset-dependent: Number Theory digit/base problems and Counting/Probability are code-solvable via enumeration or combinatorial formulas, but Geometry and Intermediate Algebra require insight chains that don't map to typed routines at all.  
- Verifier: require answer string boxing
